    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-10T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="488"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-10T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 10, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Minister for Foreign Affairs called and asked me to emphasize second
                    paragraph of my 29, February 9, 9 p.m. (although I assured him Department
                    understood situation). He said he and the President were agreed acceptance
                    wording “in compensation” would mean revolution here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
